The United States strongly condemns Iran's missile attack on the Kurdistan Region of Iraq. The attack targeted a civilian residence in Erbil, the capital city of the Kurdistan Region, without any justification. The US supports Prime Minister Kadhimi and the leaders of the Kurdistan Region in condemning this assault on Iraq's sovereignty. They promise to assist the Government of Iraq in holding Iran accountable and will support their partners in the Middle East in addressing similar threats from Iran. The US is committed to upholding Iraq's sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity.